[%# Admin + migration guide — table layout, forager counts, ENCY targets. %]
<div class="admin-only content-section">
    <h3><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Migration &amp; schema (admin)</h3>
    <p>Forager brewhouse tables are <strong>read-only</strong> via <code>DBForager</code>.
       Production ENCY stores migrated data in the targets below — never copy legacy tables into ENCY.</p>

    <div class="content-section">
        <h4>ENCY / Planning targets</h4>
        <ul class="sidebar-list">
            [% FOREACH t IN brew_feature.ency_targets %]
            <li><code>[% t | html %]</code></li>
            [% END %]
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
        <h4>Legacy forager tables &amp; Result classes</h4>
        <div class="table-container">
            <table class="data-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Legacy table</th>
                        <th>Result class</th>
                        <th>Rows (all)</th>
                        <th>Rows ([% brew_sitename | html %])</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    [% FOREACH table IN brew_feature.legacy_tables %]
                    [% SET cnt = forager_counts.$table %]
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>[% table | html %]</code></td>
                        <td><code>[% (brew_legacy_result_map.$table || '—') | html %]</code></td>
                        <td>[% IF cnt.error %]<span class="error">[% cnt.error | html %]</span>[% ELSIF forager_connected %][% cnt.total | html %][% ELSE %]—[% END %]</td>
                        <td>[% IF cnt.error %]—[% ELSIF forager_connected %][% cnt.sitename | html %][% ELSE %]—[% END %]</td>
                    </tr>
                    [% END %]
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
        [% IF forager_error %]
        <p class="error">Forager DB: [% forager_error | html %]</p>
        [% ELSIF !forager_connected %]
        <p class="text-muted">Connect <code>DBForager</code> to preview live row counts during migration.</p>
        [% END %]
    </div>

    [% IF brew_feature.legacy_results %]
    <div class="content-section">
        <h4>DBIx::Class Result files</h4>
        <ul class="sidebar-list">
            [% FOREACH r IN brew_feature.legacy_results %]
            <li><code>[% r | html %]</code></li>
            [% END %]
        </ul>
    </div>
    [% END %]

    [% IF brew_feature.relationships %]
    <div class="content-section">
        <h4>Relationships</h4>
        <ul class="sidebar-list">
            [% FOREACH rel IN brew_feature.relationships %]
            <li>[% rel | html %]</li>
            [% END %]
        </ul>
    </div>
    [% END %]

    [% IF brew_feature.migration_steps %]
    <div class="content-section">
        <h4>Migration steps (AI / admin checklist)</h4>
        <ol>
            [% FOREACH step IN brew_feature.migration_steps %]
            <li>[% step | html %]</li>
            [% END %]
        </ol>
    </div>
    [% END %]

    [% IF brew_import_preview %]
        [% INCLUDE 'Brew/_import_preview.tt' %]
    [% ELSE %]
    <p class="text-muted">Sign in as admin to see field maps and legacy record previews.</p>
    [% END %]
</div>

[%# Brew accounting + BOM + ingredient catalog seed (the reusable template) %]
<div class="admin-only content-section" style="border:1px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb;padding:12px;border-radius:6px;margin-top:12px;">
    <h3 style="margin-top:0;"><i class="fas fa-boxes"></i> Brew Accounting + BOM Starter Catalog</h3>
    <p>
        The <strong>accounting part (including BOMs)</strong> is provided as a reusable template.
        When a user/site enables the Brew addon, provisioning creates the accounting DB from the template,
        then this catalog seeds standard brewing ingredients with sample costs/prices plus an example BOM kit.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Recipes are real data</strong> (including Gambrinus-style and other authentic formulas) but are
        <em>not</em> auto-included for new users. Admins can browse them here / on the import page and
        selectively import the ones a new brewer actually wants.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="[% c.uri_for('/Inventory/seed_brew_ingredients', { sitename => brew_sitename }) %]"
           class="btn btn-primary" style="background:#92400e;border-color:#92400e;">
            Seed Brew Ingredients + Prices + Example BOM for [% brew_sitename | html %]
        </a>
        <span style="font-size:0.85em;margin-left:8px;color:#78350f;">(idempotent — safe to re-run; adjusts missing prices)</span>
    </p>
    <p style="font-size:0.8em;color:#854d0e;">
        After seeding, go to <a href="[% c.uri_for('/Inventory/items', { sitename => brew_sitename }) %]">Inventory → Items</a>
        to review/adjust the Gambrinus and other ingredient prices, then build your own recipe BOMs or kits.
    </p>
</div>